item.title: Nulls, Nulls, Nulls
item.dc:creator: @TeleNubby TeleNubby
item.description:
@TeleNubby wrote:

  1. They can lag your server if they aren’t handled properly.
  2. Because somebody did not go through a complete connection to your server.
  3. You’ll have to add checks or implement a new method of logging in - one that makes sure the connection goes through everything needed before actually creating a new player.

item.title: Nulls, Nulls, Nulls
item.dc:creator: @mo0shy mo0shy
item.description:
@mo0shy wrote:

1: Do they lag server - Yes.

2: Why are they there - An invalid source, or number, sometimes packet. In this case, the nulls are set there as actual players, but they’re not really players. Therefore you playing on the server by yourself would make it perform as though 10 people were actually on the server

3: Can I get rid of them - Yes. Search for an anti-null.
